## TypeScript me Maps

`Map` एक ऐसा object है जो key-value pairs store करता है. 

**Key** किसी भी datatype हो सकती है (string, number, object, etc.) और **Value** भी किसी भी datatype हो सकती है. 

**Example:**

```typescript
//  Map बनाने ka  tarika
const studentMarks: Map<string, number> = new Map();

//  key-value pair add karna
studentMarks.set("John", 85);
studentMarks.set("Jane", 90);
studentMarks.set("Peter", 78);

//  value access karna
console.log(studentMarks.get("John")); // Output: 85

//  Map ke saare elements print karna
console.log(studentMarks); // Output: Map(3) { 'John' => 85, 'Jane' => 90, 'Peter' => 78 }

//  Map ke size check karna
console.log(studentMarks.size); // Output: 3

//  Map me key check karna
console.log(studentMarks.has("John")); // Output: true

//  Map se key delete karna
studentMarks.delete("John");
console.log(studentMarks); // Output: Map(2) { 'Jane' => 90, 'Peter' => 78 }
```

